Hope College is a private Christian liberal college located in western Michigan. The campus is near an historic downtown. You know the ones. Old department store signs fading on exposed brick exteriors, hotels converted to assisted living facilities and one-off coffee shops meant to keep the collegiate youth buzzing from orientation to midterms to finals. It’s in the town of Holland and touts its Dutch heritage.
